description.value:
The Healthy Obese Project (HOP) is a BioSHaRE-EU core project which aims to evaluate the prevalence of the metabolically healthy obese, assess lifestyle determinants and clinical consequences of healthy obesity and explore genetic modifications and advanced metabolic profiling related to both the determinants and consequences of healthy obesity. The project is organised into study phases that each assess specific research questions. The phase 1 focus on the evaluation of the prevalence of healthy obesity and the phase 2 on the assessment of the lifestyle risk factors of healthy obesity.

#### Population Targeted

Adults from the general population aged between 18 and 80

#### Criteria used in the selection of DataSchema variables

* The variable is relevant to research questions adressed;
* The variable may potentially be used for a wide range of cohorts;
* The variable can be obtained in a valid reliable way;
* The variable is selected if it is of primary interest in its own right or if it effects other variables through confounding or bias.
